coins.obversedesign: Modern portrait of Marianne, the personification of the French Republic
coins.subject: In France, a competition was organised in 1996-1997 to choose the design of the national sides of the euro coins. A panel, chaired by the Minister for Economic and Financial Affairs and made up of experts in numismatics, artists, members of parliament, one former member of the European Commission (Christine Scrivener), the French Mint Director Emmanuel Constans, the General Engraver Pierre Rodier, actress Irène Jacob and members of professional bodies, chose the winning designs from over 1 200 entries received from 97 participants.

A panel, chaired by the Minister for Economic and Financial Affairs and made up of experts in numismatics, artists, members of parliament, one former member of the European Commission (Christine Scrivener), the French Mint Director Emmanuel Constans, the General Engraver Pierre Rodier, actress Irène Jacob and members of professional bodies, chose the winning designs from over 1 200 entries received from 97 participants.

A panel, chaired by the Minister for Economic and Financial Affairs and made up of experts in numismatics, artists, members of parliament, one former member of the European Commission (Christine Scrivener), the French Mint Director Emmanuel Constans, the General Engraver Pierre Rodier, actress Irène Jacob and members of professional bodies, chose the winning designs from over 1 200 entries received from 97 participants.
